    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-10-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-10-17T18:00:00-05:00" n="786"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d786">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.55/118: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul General at Jerusalem</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wadsworth</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-10-17T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >October 17, 1938—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>According to paragraph 7 of the enclosure to your despatch No. 556 of March 19,
                    1938, there was left open for later consideration by the British Government the
                    procedure to be adopted after September 30, 1938, concerning the power of
                    prescription to be exercised by the <pb facs="0969" n="961" xml:id="pg_961"/>
                    High Commissioner under Section 5<hi rend="italic">a</hi> of the Palestine
                    Immigration Ordinance.</p>
                <p>The Department would appreciate receiving by telegraph any information you may be
                    able discreetly to obtain, together with your comments, concerning the action if
                    any which may have been taken or may be under consideration in this matter.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
